data.meta_description: Prince Valdemar of Denmark (1858 â€“ 1939) member of the Danish Royal Family, the youngest son of Christian IX of Denmark. He married Princess Marie d'Orleans. The wedding was believed to have been politically arranged  in France by the Count of Paris (the bride's uncle). He had a lifelong naval career, but things could have been much different for the prince. He was offered two European thrones, those of Bulgaria & Norway, but declined them due to international pressures.
